## SECTION 9 — WRITING INSTRUCTIONS

> **Post gen instruction:** Follow these rules for every paragraph of body copy without exception.

1. **Conversion copy only** — every sentence moves this buyer toward picking a gift and buying it before Christmas
2. **Lead with who it's for** — every section opens with the gift-recipient profile, not the product specs
3. **Buyer phrases from Section 5** — use them naturally; speak like a friend who knows nail tools
4. **Address buying objections directly** — especially the lamp requirement and shipping timeline
5. **Honest cons build trust** — include them per product, then explain why the product is still the right buy
6. **Discount placement** — mention OFF8 or MSOFF15 near CTAs; never as a standalone line
7. **Primary keyword in `<strong>` tags** — every single mention, no exceptions
8. **No literary hooks** — open sections with the buyer benefit or gift decision, not creative preamble
9. **H2 sections are punchy** — buyers scan, they do not read long intros to sections
10. **Conclusion = final push to purchase** — remind of discount, remind of shipping, give one clear CTA
11. **Internal links mid-post only** — after first product CTA, anchor text natural, never forced
12. **No related articles section** — site component handles this
13. **American English throughout** — not British
14. **No banned phrases:** no "elevate", "seamlessly", "game-changing", "dive into", "transformative"
15. **No long em dashes** — use comma or restructure
16. **No "we tested" language** — all editorial observation based on specs and verified buyer reviews
17. **Vary sentence rhythm** — short punchy lines for selling points, longer lines for context
18. **GEO signals near CTAs** — "ships free to the US", "order before Christmas for guaranteed delivery"
